SIMPLE: subvert
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subvert
<hw>Sub*vert"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Subverted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Subverting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>subvertere</ets>,
<ets>subversum</ets>; <ets>sub</ets> under + <ets>vertere</ets> to turn:
cf. F. <ets>subvertir</ets>. See <er>Verse</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To overturn from the foundation; to overthrow; to ruin
utterly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These are his substance, sinews, arms, and strength,⟦br⟧
With which he yoketh your rebellious necks,⟦br⟧
Razeth your cities, and <qex>subverts</qex> your towns.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This would <qex>subvert</qex> the principles of all knowledge.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To pervert, as the mind, and turn it from the truth;
to corrupt; to confound.</def> <rj><au>2 Tim. iii. 14.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To overturn; overthrow; destroy; invert; reverse;
extinguish.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subvert</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Subvert
<hw>Sub*vert"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To overthrow
anything from the foundation; to be subversive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They have a power given to them like that of the evil principle,
to <qex>subvert</qex> and destroy.</q>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subvertant</ent>⟦br⟧
